        <h2>The Dangerous Years (1950-1970)</h2>
        <p>When F1 started in 1950, it was incredibly dangerous. Drivers raced in simple shirts with leather helmets. There were no seatbelts, and tracks were lined with trees and ditches.</p>
        <p><strong>Juan Manuel Fangio</strong> was the hero of this era, winning 5 titles in 7 years. In the 1960s, teams like Lotus introduced <em>aerodynamics</em> (wings) to push the cars into the ground for more grip.</p>
