        <h2>The Turbo & Tech Era (1980-1999)</h2>
        <p>Engines became smaller but much more powerful using Turbochargers, reaching over 1000 horsepower. This era was defined by the rivalry between <strong>Ayrton Senna</strong> and <strong>Alain Prost</strong>.</p>
        <p>Following the tragic death of Senna in 1994, the sport underwent a massive safety revolution, introducing stronger crash structures and better helmets.</p>
