        <h2>The Hybrid Era (2014-Present)</h2>
        <p>In 2014, F1 switched to V6 Turbo Hybrid engines. These are the most efficient engines in the world, recovering energy from heat and braking to charge a battery.</p>
        <p>Mercedes dominated this era with <strong>Lewis Hamilton</strong>, winning 8 consecutive team titles. Recently, Red Bull and <strong>Max Verstappen</strong> raised the bar for perfection.</p>
