    <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">Technical Insight: Why are they so fast?</h2>
    <div class="grid-3">
        <div>
            <h3>Downforce</h3>
            <p>F1 cars are shaped like upside-down airplane wings. Instead of lifting off, the air pushes them down, allowing them to take corners at 180mph.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h3>G-Force</h3>
            <p>When braking or turning, drivers experience up to 5G or 6G. That means their head feels 6 times heavier than normal! They need massive neck strength.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h3>The Halo</h3>
            <p>Introduced in 2018, the Titanium "Halo" bar sits above the cockpit. It can withstand the weight of a London Double Decker bus and has saved many lives.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
